  "texts": [
    "It seems that although providing people with incentives did increase their time, it did not significantly improve their performance.",
    "To further examine the association between time and quality of reappraisal, we regressed time spent across all qualities on all four dimensions.",
    "Similar to our observations from Study 1, we found a significant association between time and quality on all dimensions (see Supplemental Materials for full models).",
    "The current set of analyses suggest that across all incentives, participants who took more time produced better reappraisals.",
    "On the contrary, incentivizing participants to improve their reappraisals did lead to impact in time and to an increase of 15-24 seconds but did not lead to an improvement in reappraisal."
  ],
